<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-11-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                            <head>495. Message From Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_ERHSA1" type="from">Eden</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1" type="to">Eisenhower</persName><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d495fn1">Source: Eisenhower Library,
                                    Whitman File, International File. Secret.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-11-04"><hi rend="italic">November 4,
                                        1956</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Friend</hi>: I am sending you a personal
                                message to explain why, although we welcome the request to the
                                Secretary-General contained in the Canadian resolution, we find it
                                impossible to accept the Afro-Asian resolution. I send you this
                                preliminary notice remembering the last occasion, when owing to
                                cyphering delays my message failed to reach you before our
                                announcement was made.<note n="2" xml:id="d495fn2">Reference is
                                    presumably to <persName corresp="#p_ERHSA1">Eden</persName>’s
                                    message to <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> of
                                    October 30, <ref target="#d421">Document 421</ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>Yours ever,</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_ERHSA1"><hi rend="strong">Anthony</hi></persName><note n="3" xml:id="d495fn3">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                                    signature.</note></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>